                            <comment id="13384" author="nedbass" created="Wed, 27 Apr 2011 11:36:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With this patch I get a broken kernel dependency on RHEL6:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$ rpm -qRp lustre-modules-2.0.59-2.6.32_132.6chaos.ch5.x86_64_gd160b97.x86_64.rpm | grep kernel&lt;br/&gt;
kernel = %&lt;/p&gt;
{krequires}

&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t we need to restore the krequires definition, which was removed in commit 086ff8c46009479bfdac9f570331a6c93b7d52ac?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;%define krequires %(bash -c &quot;echo %&lt;/p&gt;
{kversion}
&lt;p&gt; | sed -e &apos;s/.x86_64$//&apos; -e &apos;s/.i586$//&apos; -e &apos;s/-smp$//&apos; -e &apos;s/-bigsmp$//&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
